# SECRETARY_APPROVERS — GitHub usernames authorized to approve any publication
# type (Final, Errata, Implementers Drafts, Drafts) in this repository.
#
# Why a file and not a GitHub team query: the publish-prep workflow needs to
# verify the reviewer is on the OIDF secretary team. Looking up team membership
# requires a token with org-scoped `read:org`, which the default GITHUB_TOKEN
# does not have. Rather than introduce a PAT or a GitHub App, the workflow
# reads this file (from `main`, never from the PR branch) and checks the
# reviewer's username against it.
#
# If you're on the secretary team but not listed here: your APPROVED review
# will be treated as a co-chair / editor approval. Drafts can still publish if
# all checks pass, but Final / Errata / Implementers Drafts will be blocked
# with a comment asking for a review from @openid/secretaryandteam.
#
# Keep in sync with @openid/secretaryandteam. One username per line.

